# Carve Field Guide

This document is a *working reference*: one plain-text Carve source that exercises
(nearly) every construct the renderer supports, then prints to a clean PDF. It doubles
as the coffee handbook for /Carve Coffee Roasters/ --- because a reference is easier to
read when it actually says something.

Text carries the usual inline marks: *bold*, /italic/, _underline_, {=highlighted=},
{+inserted+}, {-deleted-}, ~struck~, `inline code`, super{^script^} and sub{,script,},
plus an abbreviation like HTML and a keyboard hint :kbd[Ctrl] + :kbd[C]. Smart typography
turns "straight quotes" curly, 'single' too, and --- / -- into proper dashes.

*[HTML]: HyperText Markup Language

## Origin and tasting

Coffees from a /single/ farm, washing station, or co-operative --- never blended. Each
lot tastes of its place: the soil, the altitude, the process.

![Roast levels from light to French](roast.svg)
^ Figure 1: the four roast stages, lightest to darkest

> We roast light to let origin speak. No dark, no bitter, no hiding behind the roast ---
> only the character of the bean.
>
> > And yes, that is a nested blockquote.

::: note "House style"
New lots land every few weeks. Roast dates are printed on every bag, and we ship within
48 hours of roasting.
:::

The address on every bag, as a line block:

::: |
Carve Coffee Roasters
14 Kaffeegasse
Vienna, AT
:::

## Brew methods

Ordered steps for a pour-over (note the list starts at 1, then a custom-start list):

1. Rinse the filter, preheat the carafe.
2. Add grounds, make a shallow well.
3. Bloom with twice the coffee weight.

Continuing the same recipe, renumbered:

4. Pour in slow, steady spirals.
5. Let it draw down fully.

A checklist you can actually tick:

- [x] beans weighed
- [x] water at 94 °C
- [ ] second pour
- [ ] tasted and logged

A pipe table with per-column alignment:

|= Method    |=> Ratio |=~ Grind      |
| V60        |    1:16 |  Medium-fine |
| Aeropress  |    1:14 |  Fine        |
| Batch brew |    1:17 |  Medium      |

The same data as a `list-table` (renders to a real table under the faithful renderer):

{header-rows=1}
::: list-table "Recipe by method"
- - Method
  - Time
- - V60
  - 2:45
- - Aeropress
  - 1:30
:::

::: tip "Brew it bright"
Keep the water just off the boil (94 °C) and don't over-extract --- the florals fade fast.
:::

::: warning "Storage"
Keep the bag sealed and away from light. Whole bean stays bright for about three weeks.
:::

A Mermaid diagram (typeset to SVG at print time):

``` mermaid
graph LR
  G[Green beans] --> R[Roast]
  R --> D[Rest 3-7 days]
  D --> B{Brew}
  B -->|pour-over| V[V60]
  B -->|immersion| A[Aeropress]
```

## Reference

A definition list:

:: Washed
:: Natural
:  Fruit removed before drying --- clean, bright cups.
:  Dried in the whole cherry --- heavier, fruit-forward cups.

