## Notes and fine print

Footnotes come in two flavors: a referenced note[^ratio] and an inline one[the grind
matters as much as the ratio]{.fn}.

[^ratio]: A 1:16 ratio means 1 g of coffee to 16 g of water.

A collapsible detail (open in print):

::: details "Why rest coffee after roasting?"
Fresh-roasted beans off-gas CO2, which disrupts extraction. A 3--7 day rest lets the gas
settle so the brew tastes even.
:::

A block spoiler and an inline :spoiler[hidden tasting note]:

::: spoiler "Cupping score"
This lot scored 87.5 on the SCA scale.
:::

::: danger "Never do this"
Do not brew with boiling water straight off the heat --- it scorches delicate florals.
:::

::: info "Did you know"
Autolinked bare URLs work too: https://github.com/markup-carve/carve-php
:::

::: success "You're set"
Grind, brew, taste, adjust. Then do it again tomorrow.
:::

You can @mention a roaster or tag a #single-origin topic inline, and reference-style
links like [our brew guide][guide] resolve from a definition at the bottom.

